7: Hello? Can we get a table?
10:
That's weird. Pretty sure this is a
restaurant...
14:
If they're closed, they're closed. Let's
just go somewhere else. I'm starving.
17:
That's the thing, though. The sign out
front said they're open...
34:
The body is still warm. Not much
time has passed since his death...
37: You there! What're you doing here?!
39: Wait... Did you kill that man?
45:
Oh yeah? You can tell us all about it
down at the station.
48:
We're tellin' you, we didn't do it! And
we're not going anywhere!
52:
P-patience, everyone. Surely if we
explain our situation, these rational
young men will believe us!
61:
Big talk back there for a little bunny.
Those punks threw us in the
slammer without another word.
66:
Indeed, I was too naïve. Those fiends
didn't even bother with an
investigation.
74:
You think we're gonna find us a
good lawyer here? At this rate, we're
as good as executed.
79:
But we didn't do it! And the criminal
is still out there! They can't do this!
83:
They sure as hell can. I say we knock
out the guard and blow this joint.
88:
Are you mad?! That'll only make us
look more suspicious!
93:
Keep it down, would you? I'm nursing
one hell of a hangover.
106:
The hell's a detective doing in the
slammer?
110:
Same reason as you lot. I was
framed.
112:
Well? What do you say, neighbors?
Want me to prove your innocence?
115:
I will, of course, expect some form of
compensation.
119:
What do you expect to do from the
inside of a cell?
123:
Heh, I have to leave some things up
to your imagination, don't I? Now,
why don't you tell me your story?
We've got all the time in the world...
128:
And that's what happened. Do you
think you can solve the case?
132: Hey! Hey, you! Go grab your boss!
135: The hell're you yellin' about now?!
137:
Those four inmates are innocent.
The real culprit is...
147:
Wait, what?! Did you just... shoot
them?!
151:
Well, yeah, they're the bad guys,
right? Besides, these bullets aren't
lethal. They just got a heavy dose of
my sleeping potion.
156:
D-don't tell me THAT'S how you solve
cases! Where's your proof?
161:
You want proof? Here. Looks like the
stiff owed these guys some money.
Happy?
164:
Now... Wasn't that faster than
waiting for a lawyer?
168:
Yeah, sure, if we prioritize efficiency
over HUMAN DECENCY.
172:
Anyway, I think it's time we
skedaddle.
178:
Well, that explains it. The victim
owed those men money, so they
killed him. Then they just needed
someone to pin the blame on.
180:
You lot just happened to be the first
people that came by.
183: Is that what happened to you too?
187: Nope. I was caught skipping the bill.
192: Then you're not innocent at all!
196:
In any case, I can't exactly show my
face around here. Come on, let's go.
201:
Indeed. Let's go back to Starview
Village. We will welcome you with
open arms.
210:
Remember our deal? I expect
compensation for busting you out.
And it just so happens I need a
place to hide.
214:
Haha, you should see your faces.
You've got nothing to worry about.
